abstract: The Midwestern centrists are the only two plausible not-Biden candidates.
snippet: The Midwestern centrists are the only two plausible not-Biden candidates.
lead_paragraph: The ridiculous number of candidates on the Democratic stage last night created a fundamentally misleading aural and visual impression. Watching without access to polling data, you might have imagined that this was some sort of wild careening mess of a primary race, when really itâ€™s remarkably consolidated.

headline_main: Democratic Debate Like a Nightclub on a Tuesday, Trevor Noah Says

abstract: Elizabeth Warren was called out by rivals for a change, Joe Biden failed to stand out and Bernie Sanders calmed concerns about his health. Pete Buttigieg had his biggest night yet.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren was called out by rivals for a change, Joe Biden failed to stand out and Bernie Sanders calmed concerns about his health. Pete Buttigieg had his biggest night yet.
lead_paragraph: WESTERVILLE, Ohio â€” The CNN/New York Times debate on Tuesday night revealed new dynamics in the Democratic presidential race: Senator Elizabeth Warren took sustained fire from multiple rivals, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. struggled to make an impact and Mayor Pete Buttigieg and other candidates were newly aggressive in making their points.

headline_main: 6 Takeaways From the October Democratic Debate
byline_original: By Shane Goldmacher and Reid J. Epstein

abstract: After decades of trying to prove their toughness on national security, the candidates described an allies-first, tough-on-Russia foreign policy. But many of them, too, want to withdraw from the Middle East.
snippet: After decades of trying to prove their toughness on national security, the candidates described an allies-first, tough-on-Russia foreign policy. But many of them, too, want to withdraw from the Middle East.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON â€” For nearly two decades, Republicans have dominated national security debates, portraying themselves as tough on terrorists after the Sept. 11, 2001, attacks and tough on a recalcitrant, disruptive Russia. On Tuesday night, Democrats sensed an opportunity to retake that ground, attacking President Trumpâ€™s impulsive action in Syria as a gift to the Islamic State and to President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia.
